# Landing Page Cursor Rules

## Page Structure (Top to Bottom)
1. **Navigation**: Logo, links, CTA button (sticky)
2. **Hero**: Headline, sub-headline, primary CTA, hero image/video
3. **Social Proof**: Logos, testimonials, stats
4. **Features**: 3-6 key features with icons and descriptions
5. **How It Works**: 3-step process illustration
6. **Pricing**: Plan comparison table with recommended plan highlighted
7. **Testimonials**: Customer quotes with photos
8. **FAQ**: Expandable accordion
9. **Final CTA**: Repeat call-to-action
10. **Footer**: Links, legal, social media

## Design Rules
- One primary CTA per section (don't overwhelm)
- Use contrast for CTA buttons (stand out from page)
- Above-the-fold must communicate value proposition in 5 seconds
- Use whitespace generously — don't cram content
- Mobile-first responsive design

## SEO
- Unique `<title>` and `<meta description>` per page
- One `<h1>` per page (your main value proposition)
- Use structured data (JSON-LD) for organization/product
- Optimize Core Web Vitals (LCP, CLS, INP)
- Use semantic HTML throughout

## Conversion Optimization
- Clear value proposition above the fold
- Reduce friction: minimal form fields
- Add urgency/scarcity when appropriate (honestly)
- Show trust signals: security badges, guarantees, reviews
- A/B test headlines and CTAs
